description:
Complete Cursor Guide with Kehan Zhang

This is the Complete Cursor Guide with Kehan Zhang, one of the best developers out there, who uses Cursor extensively. In this comprehensive course, learn how to confidently use Cursor to code landing pages, desktop apps, and more. No prior programming knowledge needed â€“ just a computer.
 In this video:
-we cover everything from the basics to advanced features of Cursor 2.0
-how to transform it into a full-stack app
-and how to compare it with other vibe coding tools like Replit, V0, and Lovable. 

Try out using Vibecode here (get your first 3 apps free): https://vibecode.go.link/9ADNT

Try out the meme generator we creator in this video: https://meme-generator-one-psi.vercel.app/

Our socials:

comments.text: Well, might want to lay off the coffee..  Hah!  Anyway, yes, this is an AI coding channel, if you're not into AI coding, then this channel isn't for you.  As an aside, local LLM's are great for specific use cases (summarizing your emails, role-playing, knowledge retrieval), but they are not there for coding, especially if you don't own a 10k dollar computer.  You need large models with large context windows, and you aren't going to get anywhere with your bog standard gaming rig with 8gb of VRAM.   I can guarantee that you can't make anything remotely similar with LM Studio and a free Llama 14b model with 32k context window.  If you think the coding from something like Sonnet 4.5 or GPT 5 is even in the same ballpark as local llm's, you clearly haven't used them in a long time (and probably why you think llm's are so bad at coding, because you've only used local llms).
